interpretation: The "woman in manual wheelchair" card represents the need for adaptability and resilience. It suggests that the querent may be facing challenges or obstacles, but they have the strength and determination to overcome them. This card reminds us to focus on our abilities rather than our limitations, and to be resourceful in finding solutions to problems. The woman in the manual wheelchair is also a symbol of independence and self-reliance, indicating that the querent may need to rely on their own inner strength to achieve their goals. Keywords associated with this card include adaptability, resilience, strength, determination, resourcefulness, independence, and self-reliance. Overall, this card encourages the querent to embrace their challenges and trust in their ability to overcome them.
